title: C-AlRuNi (Al$_{20}$Ni$_{3}$Ru$_{5}$) Structure
comments:
Most of these sites are partially or contained a mixture of species.  We label them by the majority species: \begin{itemize} \item Ni-I (1a) is 79\% nickel and 21\% ruthenium, \item Ni-II (1b) is 100\% nickel, \item Al-I (3c) is 77\% aluminum and 23\% vacancies, \item Ru-I (6g) is 81.4\% ruthenium and 18.6\% nickel, \item Al-II (8i) is 74\% aluminum and 26\% vacancies, and \item Al-III (12k) is 100\% aluminum. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 This gives an actual composition of Al$_{20.23}$Ni$_{2.906}$Ru$_{5.094}$, which we simplify to Al$_{20}$Ni$_{3}$Ru$_{5}$.
